keywords spirebound conclave
---
The Spirebound Conclave was a mountain academy in the Cinderteeth Range chartered to preserve dangerous magical knowledge.
Founding doctrine of Continuance: no discovery, oath, or lesson should die with its keeper.

Three factions: Ember Canon (will through fire), Prism Thesis (memory through crystal), Pale Ledger (testimony through spirit imprinting).

Initially scholarly. When border wars severed supply routes, Continuance became a survival engine.
Volunteers were replaced by condemned debtors transferred under sealed warrants from Midgaard and proto-Kowloon.
Experiments produced Flamebound Sentinels (fire-bound veterans), Shadow Stalkers (uncontrollable scouts), and Spirit Mages (chained mnemonic echoes).

The Prism Thesis conducted field trials in remote forests, implanting resonance crystals in root systems.
Unretrieved crystals warped surrounding ecology into the Withered Depths over centuries.
The Blightmother may be the final product of an unsupervised Conclave process.

Collapse: rival offices sabotaged each other's containment during a seismic event.
Regional powers buried the sanctum by policy. No recovery team was sent.
Their crimes created the Rivennid, fed the Withered Depths, and left Midgaard and Kowloon sharing unspoken guilt.
